usdPppMIB.name: usdPppMIB

revisions.description: Added new objects to usdPppIpGroup, usdPppLcpGroup and usdPppMlpppGroup.
Added usdPppLinkConfigStandardIfIndex object for cross referencing with standard PPP mibs.
Added usdPppLinkStatusTunnelIfIndex, Multi-Link PPP support, and PPP Interface Summary counts. Modified Terminate reasons to include tunnel-related events.
Additional objects added to support remote access capabilities, including termination reason, authentication protocol, option negotiation status.
Initial version of this MIB module.

usdPppMIB.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdPppMIB.description: The Point-to-Point Protocol (PPP) MIB for the Unisphere enterprise.

UsdPppAuthentication.name: UsdPppAuthentication
UsdPppAuthentication.description: Specifies the type(s) of PPP authentication used, if any: none No authentication is negotiated. pap PAP negotiation only. chap CHAP negotiation only. papChap PAP negotiation is attempted first; if fails, attempt CHAP. chapPap CHAP negotiation is attempted first; if fails, attempt PAP.

UsdPppMlPppBundleName.name: UsdPppMlPppBundleName
UsdPppMlPppBundleName.description: MLPPP Bundle name. The bundle name is a characteristic of a MLPPP network interface.

usdPppLinkStatusTable.name: usdPppLinkStatusTable
usdPppLinkStatusTable.description: This table contains entries for PPP interfaces present in the system.

usdPppLinkStatusEntry.name: usdPppLinkStatusEntry
usdPppLinkStatusEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of a PPP interface.

usdPppLinkStatusTerminateReason.name: usdPppLinkStatusTerminateReason
usdPppLinkStatusTerminateReason.description: Reason the PPP link was terminated: none None. other Not specified. adminDisable Interface administratively disabled. lowerLayerDown Underlying interface is down. noUpperInterface No interface above PPP. authenticationFailure Authentication failed. peerTerminated Peer initiated termination. peerRenegotiated Peer initiated renegotiation. maxRetriesExceeded Maximum number of config retries exceeded. negotiationFailure Failed to negotiate LCP option. See usdPppLinkStatusTerminateNegFailOption. keepaliveFailure Keepalive failed. sessionTimeout Maximum session period expired. inactivityTimeout Maximum inactivity period expired. addressLeaseExpired Lease for network address expired. adminLogout Session administratively terminated. tunnelFailed Associated tunnel failed. tunnelDisconnected Associated tunnel disconnected. loopback Loopback detected.

usdPppLinkStatusTerminateNegFailOption.name: usdPppLinkStatusTerminateNegFailOption
usdPppLinkStatusTerminateNegFailOption.description: Reports the PPP LCP option for which negotiation failed, when usdPppLinkStatusTerminateReason has the value 'negotiationFailure'.

usdPppLinkStatusLocalMagicNumber.name: usdPppLinkStatusLocalMagicNumber
usdPppLinkStatusLocalMagicNumber.description: Magic number negotiated for the local side.

usdPppLinkStatusRemoteMagicNumber.name: usdPppLinkStatusRemoteMagicNumber
usdPppLinkStatusRemoteMagicNumber.description: Magic number negotiated for the remote side.

usdPppLinkStatusLocalAuthentication.name: usdPppLinkStatusLocalAuthentication
usdPppLinkStatusLocalAuthentication.description: Authentication protocol negotiated for the local side.

usdPppLinkStatusTunnelIfIndex.name: usdPppLinkStatusTunnelIfIndex
usdPppLinkStatusTunnelIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an associated interface pertaining to a tunneling protocol, or zero if no such interface exists. The type of tunneling interface can be identified from information in the entries in ifTable and usdIfTable for this tunnel interface.

usdPppLinkConfigTable.name: usdPppLinkConfigTable
usdPppLinkConfigTable.description: This table contains entries for PPP interfaces present in the system.

usdPppLinkConfigEntry.name: usdPppLinkConfigEntry
usdPppLinkConfigEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of a PPP interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable.

usdPppLinkConfigIfIndex.name: usdPppLinkConfigIfIndex
usdPppLinkConfigIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the PPP interface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading usdPppNextIfIndex.

usdPppLinkConfigRowStatus.name: usdPppLinkConfigRowStatus
usdPppLinkConfigRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdPppLinkConfigRowStatus usdPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: A value for usdPppLinkConfigIndex must have been determined previously, by reading usdPppNextIfIndex. The interface identified by usdPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex must exist. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable is created/destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

usdPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex.name: usdPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex
usdPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an interface over which this PPP interface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a non-zero value be configured at entry creation.

usdPppLinkConfigKeepalive.name: usdPppLinkConfigKeepalive
usdPppLinkConfigKeepalive.description: Keepalive interval in seconds. A value of zero disables keepalive. Keepalive is performed using LCP Echo.

usdPppLinkConfigAuthentication.name: usdPppLinkConfigAuthentication
usdPppLinkConfigAuthentication.description: Specifies the type(s) of authentication, if any, to be negotiated with the peer: none No authentication is negotiated. pap PAP negotiation only. chap CHAP negotiation only. papChap PAP negotiation is attempted first; if fails, attempt CHAP. chapPap CHAP negotiation is attempted first; if fails, attempt PAP. If authentication negotiation is not supported for this PPP interface, then any attempt to explicitely set this object will result in a notWritable error and it will be implicitily set to the DEFVAL on row creation. Setting this object to none will set usdPppLinkConfigAuthenticatorVirtualRouter object to an empty string.

usdPppLinkConfigMaxAuthenRetries.name: usdPppLinkConfigMaxAuthenRetries
usdPppLinkConfigMaxAuthenRetries.description: The number of authentication retries permitted, in addition to a failed initial attempt. If all retries fail, the link is reset. If authentication negotiation is not supported for this PPP interface, then any attempt to explicitely set this object will result in a notWritable error and it will be implicitily set to the DEFVAL on row creation.

usdPppLinkConfigStandardIfIndex.name: usdPppLinkConfigStandardIfIndex
usdPppLinkConfigStandardIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value for this interface in the standard PPP MIBs. The ifIndex value for PPP interfaces is not the same for both proprietary and standard MIB tables pertaining to PPP interface. Therefore this value is provide to simply cross referencing standard PPP and proprietary PPP MIB information.

usdPppLinkConfigChapMinChallengeLength.name: usdPppLinkConfigChapMinChallengeLength
usdPppLinkConfigChapMinChallengeLength.description: Minimum value of the CHAP authenticator challenge length value. This value is never allowed to be set to a value greater than usdPppLinkConfigChapMaxChallengeLength.

usdPppLinkConfigChapMaxChallengeLength.name: usdPppLinkConfigChapMaxChallengeLength
usdPppLinkConfigChapMaxChallengeLength.description: Maximum value of the CHAP authenticator challenge length value. This value is never allowed to be set to a value less than usdPppLinkConfigChapMinChallengeLength.

usdPppLinkConfigPassiveMode.name: usdPppLinkConfigPassiveMode
usdPppLinkConfigPassiveMode.description: When enabled, LCP state machine is forced into passive mode on lower layer UP message. It adds compatibility with slow and buggy clients.

usdPppLinkConfigAuthenticatorVirtualRout.name: usdPppLinkConfigAuthenticatorVirtualRouter
usdPppLinkConfigAuthenticatorVirtualRout.description: The name of the virtual router (Unisphere-Data-ROUTER-MIB.usdRouterName) to be used for authentication on the PPP interface. Setting this object statically binds the authenticating virtual router with the PPP interface. If this object is not explicitly set or it is set to null string, then this object is ignored and the virtual router used for authentication is determined by other means. On a Set operation, if the value of this object is not null and does not correspond to an existing virtual router, then an inconsistentValue error is returned. Setting this object to non null string returns inconsistentValue error if usdPppLinkConfigAuthentication object is none or not configured.

usdPppNextIfIndex.name: usdPppNextIfIndex
usdPppNextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in the usdPppLinkConfigTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

usdPppIpTable.name: usdPppIpTable
usdPppIpTable.description: Table containing the IP parameters for the local PPP entity.

usdPppIpEntry.name: usdPppIpEntry
usdPppIpEntry.description: IPCP status information for a particular PPP link.

usdPppIpServiceStatus.name: usdPppIpServiceStatus
usdPppIpServiceStatus.description: Indicates whether IP protocol service is operating over this PPP link. Service is established on this link through means outside this MIB.

usdPppIpTerminateReason.name: usdPppIpTerminateReason
usdPppIpTerminateReason.description: Reason the IPCP link was terminated: none None. other Not specified. noService No IP service configured on this PPP link. admin Administratively disabled. linkDown Underlying link is down. peerTerminated Peer initiated termination. peerRenegotiated Peer initiated renegotiation. maxRetriesExceeded Maximum number of config retries exceeded. negotiationFailure Failed to negotiate IPCP option. See usdPppIpTerminateNegFailOption.

usdPppIpTerminateNegFailOption.name: usdPppIpTerminateNegFailOption
usdPppIpTerminateNegFailOption.description: Reports the PPP IPCP option for which negotiation failed, when usdPppIpTerminateReason has the value 'negotiationFailure'.

usdPppIpLocalIpAddress.name: usdPppIpLocalIpAddress
usdPppIpLocalIpAddress.description: IP Address used by the local side.

usdPppIpRemoteIpAddress.name: usdPppIpRemoteIpAddress
usdPppIpRemoteIpAddress.description: IP Address used by the remote side.

usdPppIpRemotePrimaryDnsAddress.name: usdPppIpRemotePrimaryDnsAddress
usdPppIpRemotePrimaryDnsAddress.description: Primary DNS server used by the remote side.

usdPppIpRemoteSecondaryDnsAddress.name: usdPppIpRemoteSecondaryDnsAddress
usdPppIpRemoteSecondaryDnsAddress.description: Secondary DNS server used by the remote side.

usdPppIpRemotePrimaryWinsAddress.name: usdPppIpRemotePrimaryWinsAddress
usdPppIpRemotePrimaryWinsAddress.description: Primary WINS server used by the remote side.

usdPppIpRemoteSecondaryWinsAddress.name: usdPppIpRemoteSecondaryWinsAddress
usdPppIpRemoteSecondaryWinsAddress.description: Secondary WINS server used by the remote side.

usdPppIpConfigTable.name: usdPppIpConfigTable
usdPppIpConfigTable.description: Table containing the IP parameters for the local PPP entity.

usdPppIpConfigEntry.name: usdPppIpConfigEntry
usdPppIpConfigEntry.description: IPCP configuration information for a particular PPP link.

usdPppIpConfigPeerDnsPriority.name: usdPppIpConfigPeerDnsPriority
usdPppIpConfigPeerDnsPriority.description: When enabled, allows peer's DNS address to prevail in the event of a negotiation conflict; when disabled, the local PPP interface's DNS address prevails.

usdPppIpConfigPeerWinsPriority.name: usdPppIpConfigPeerWinsPriority
usdPppIpConfigPeerWinsPriority.description: When enabled, allows peer's WINS address to prevail in the event of a negotiation conflict; when disabled, the local PPP interface's WINS address prevails.

usdPppIpConfigIpcpNetmask.name: usdPppIpConfigIpcpNetmask
usdPppIpConfigIpcpNetmask.description: Enables the negotiation of the IPCP option netmask (0x90) during IPCP negotiation.

usdPppOsiTable.name: usdPppOsiTable
usdPppOsiTable.description: Table containing the OSI parameters for the local PPP entity.

usdPppOsiEntry.name: usdPppOsiEntry
usdPppOsiEntry.description: OSICP status information for a particular PPP link.

usdPppOsiServiceStatus.name: usdPppOsiServiceStatus
usdPppOsiServiceStatus.description: Indicates whether OSI protocol service is operating over this PPP link. Service is established on this link through means outside this MIB.

usdPppOsiOperStatus.name: usdPppOsiOperStatus
usdPppOsiOperStatus.description: The operational status of the OSI network protocol. If the value of this object is up then the finite state machine for the OSI network protocol has reached the Opened state.

usdPppOsiTerminateReason.name: usdPppOsiTerminateReason
usdPppOsiTerminateReason.description: Reason the OSICP link was terminated: none None. other Not specified. noService No OSI service configured on this PPP link. admin Administratively disabled. linkDown Underlying link is down. peerTerminated Peer initiated termination. peerRenegotiated Peer initiated renegotiation. maxRetriesExceeded Maximum number of config retries exceeded. negotiationFailure Failed to negotiate IPCP option. See usdPppOsiTerminateNegFailOption.

usdPppOsiTerminateNegFailOption.name: usdPppOsiTerminateNegFailOption
usdPppOsiTerminateNegFailOption.description: Reports the PPP OSICP option for which negotiation failed, when usdPppOsiTerminateReason has the value 'negotiationFailure'.

usdPppOsiLocalAlignNpdu.name: usdPppOsiLocalAlignNpdu
usdPppOsiLocalAlignNpdu.description: Local alignment of network PDU: none No alignment specified. oneModulo4 Alignment on first octet (out of four). twoModulo4 Alignment on second octet (out of four). threeModulo4 Alignment on third octet (out of four). fourModulo4 Alignment on fourth octet (out of four). even Alignment on even-octet boundary. odd Alignment on odd-octet boundary.

usdPppOsiRemoteAlignNpdu.name: usdPppOsiRemoteAlignNpdu
usdPppOsiRemoteAlignNpdu.description: Remote alignment of network PDU. none No alignment specified. oneModulo4 Alignment on first octet (out of four). twoModulo4 Alignment on second octet (out of four). threeModulo4 Alignment on third octet (out of four). fourModulo4 Alignment on fourth octet (out of four). even Alignment on even-octet boundary. odd Alignment on odd-octet boundary.

usdPppOsiConfigTable.name: usdPppOsiConfigTable
usdPppOsiConfigTable.description: Table containing configuration variables for the OSICP for the local PPP entity.

usdPppOsiConfigEntry.name: usdPppOsiConfigEntry
usdPppOsiConfigEntry.description: OSICP information for a particular PPP link.

usdPppOsiConfigAdminStatus.name: usdPppOsiConfigAdminStatus
usdPppOsiConfigAdminStatus.description: The immediate desired status of the OSI network protocol. Setting this object to open will inject an administrative open event into the OSI network protocol's finite state machine. Setting this object to close will inject an administrative close event into the OSI network protocol's finite state machine.

usdPppSessionTable.name: usdPppSessionTable
usdPppSessionTable.description: This table contains entries for PPP interfaces present in the system.

usdPppSessionEntry.name: usdPppSessionEntry
usdPppSessionEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of a PPP interface.

usdPppSessionGrant.name: usdPppSessionGrant
usdPppSessionGrant.description: Indicates whether a session has been granted via the authentication mechanism.

usdPppSessionTerminateReason.name: usdPppSessionTerminateReason
usdPppSessionTerminateReason.description: The reason the session was terminated.

usdPppSessionStartTime.name: usdPppSessionStartTime
usdPppSessionStartTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this session last became active.

usdPppSessionInOctets.name: usdPppSessionInOctets
usdPppSessionInOctets.description: Number of octets received since this session last became active, as denoted by usdPppSessionStartTime.

usdPppSessionOutOctets.name: usdPppSessionOutOctets
usdPppSessionOutOctets.description: Number of octets sent since this session last became active, as denoted by usdPppSessionStartTime.

usdPppSessionInPackets.name: usdPppSessionInPackets
usdPppSessionInPackets.description: Number of packets received since this session last became active, as denoted by usdPppSessionStartTime.

usdPppSessionOutPackets.name: usdPppSessionOutPackets
usdPppSessionOutPackets.description: Number of packets sent since this session last became active, as denoted by usdPppSessionStartTime.

usdPppSessionSessionTimeout.name: usdPppSessionSessionTimeout
usdPppSessionSessionTimeout.description: Maximum duration for the session, after which the session terminates automatically.

usdPppSessionInactivityTimeout.name: usdPppSessionInactivityTimeout
usdPppSessionInactivityTimeout.description: Maximum inactivity duration for the session, after which the session terminates automatically.

usdPppSessionAccountingInterval.name: usdPppSessionAccountingInterval
usdPppSessionAccountingInterval.description: Interval that must elapse between generation of accounting records for this session.

usdPppSessionRemoteIpAddress.name: usdPppSessionRemoteIpAddress
usdPppSessionRemoteIpAddress.description: Remote IP address, obtained from the authentication service, to be used during IPCP negotiation with the remote side.

usdPppSessionRemotePrimaryDnsAddress.name: usdPppSessionRemotePrimaryDnsAddress
usdPppSessionRemotePrimaryDnsAddress.description: Remote primary DNS IP address, obtained from the authentication service, to be used during IPCP negotiation with the remote side.

usdPppSessionRemoteSecondaryDnsAddress.name: usdPppSessionRemoteSecondaryDnsAddress
usdPppSessionRemoteSecondaryDnsAddress.description: Remote secondary DNS IP address, obtained from the authentication service, to be used during IPCP negotiation with the remote side.

usdPppSessionRemotePrimaryWinsAddress.name: usdPppSessionRemotePrimaryWinsAddress
usdPppSessionRemotePrimaryWinsAddress.description: Remote primary WINS IP address, obtained from the authentication service, to be used during IPCP negotiation with the remote side.

usdPppSessionRemoteSecondaryWinsAddress.name: usdPppSessionRemoteSecondaryWinsAddress
usdPppSessionRemoteSecondaryWinsAddress.description: Remote secondary WINS IP address, obtained from the authentication service, to be used during IPCP negotiation with the remote side.

usdPppMlPppBundleTable.name: usdPppMlPppBundleTable
usdPppMlPppBundleTable.description: This table contains entries for MLPPP bundles present in the system.

usdPppMlPppBundleEntry.name: usdPppMlPppBundleEntry
usdPppMlPppBundleEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of a MLPPP bundle.

usdPppMlPppBundleName.name: usdPppMlPppBundleName
usdPppMlPppBundleName.description: The administrative name of the MLPPP bundle associated with this MLPPP network interface.

usdPppMlPppBundleRowStatus.name: usdPppMlPppBundleRowStatus
usdPppMlPppBundleRowStatus.description: The rowStatus for this entry. The following sets are supported: createAndGo(4), destroy(6) The following values can be read from this object: active(1)

usdPppMlPppBundleNetworkIfIndex.name: usdPppMlPppBundleNetworkIfIndex
usdPppMlPppBundleNetworkIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of this MLPPP network interface. It is a valid ifIndex even if there is no corresponding network interface instance in the usdPppMlPppLinkConfigTable.

usdPppMlPppNextLinkIfIndex.name: usdPppMlPppNextLinkIfIndex
usdPppMlPppNextLinkIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in usdPppMlPppLinkConfigTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

usdPppMlPppLinkConfigTable.name: usdPppMlPppLinkConfigTable
usdPppMlPppLinkConfigTable.description: This table contains entries for MLPPP interfaces present in the system.

usdPppMlPppLinkConfigEntry.name: usdPppMlPppLinkConfigEntry
usdPppMlPppLinkConfigEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of MLPPP interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable.

usdPppMlPppLinkConfigIfIndex.name: usdPppMlPppLinkConfigIfIndex
usdPppMlPppLinkConfigIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the MLPPP interface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading usdPppMlPppNextLinkIfIndex.

usdPppMlPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex.name: usdPppMlPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex
usdPppMlPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an interface over which this PPP interface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a non-zero value be configured at entry creation.

usdPppMlPppLinkConfigKeepalive.name: usdPppMlPppLinkConfigKeepalive
usdPppMlPppLinkConfigKeepalive.description: Keepalive interval in seconds. A value of zero disables keepalive. Keepalive is performed using LCP Echo.

usdPppMlPppLinkConfigAuthentication.name: usdPppMlPppLinkConfigAuthentication
usdPppMlPppLinkConfigAuthentication.description: Specifies the type(s) of authentication, if any, to be negotiated with the peer: none No authentication is negotiated. pap PAP negotiation only. chap CHAP negotiation only. papChap PAP negotiation is attempted first; if fails, attempt CHAP. chapPap CHAP negotiation is attempted first; if fails, attempt PAP.

usdPppMlPppLinkConfigMaxAuthenRetries.name: usdPppMlPppLinkConfigMaxAuthenRetries
usdPppMlPppLinkConfigMaxAuthenRetries.description: The number of authentication retries permitted, in addition to a failed initial attempt. If all retries fail, the link is reset.

usdPppMlPppLinkConfigRowStatus.name: usdPppMlPppLinkConfigRowStatus
usdPppMlPppLinkConfigRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdPppMlPppLinkConfigRowStatus usdPppMlPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: A value for usdPppMlPppLinkConfigIndex must have been determined previously, by reading usdPppMlPppNextIfIndex. The interface identified by usdPppMlPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex must exist. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable is created/destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

usdPppMlPppNextNetworkIfIndex.name: usdPppMlPppNextNetworkIfIndex
usdPppMlPppNextNetworkIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigTable.name: usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigTable
usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigTable.description: This table contains entries for MLPPP network interfaces present in the system.

usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigEntry.name: usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigEntry
usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of MLPPP interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable.

usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigIfIndex.name: usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigIfIndex
usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the MLPPP network interface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading usdPppMlPppNextNetworkIfIndex.

usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigLowerIfIndex.name: usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigLowerIfIndex
usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of a PPP link interface over which this PPP network interface is to be layered. On sets, the value of this object must equal on of the previously created PPP link interfaces created in the usdPppMlPppLinkConfigTable. On gets, the value of this object is the lexicographically least PPP link interface in a potential bundle of PPP link interfaces.

usdPppMlPppNetworkBundleName.name: usdPppMlPppNetworkBundleName
usdPppMlPppNetworkBundleName.description: The MLPPP bundle name administratively assigned.

usdPppMlPppNetworkRowStatus.name: usdPppMlPppNetworkRowStatus
usdPppMlPppNetworkRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigLowerIfIndex usdPppMlPppNetworkBundleName usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigRowStatus In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: A value for usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigIndex must have been determined previously, by reading usdPppMlPppNextNetworkIfIndex. The interface identified by usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigLowerIfIndex must exist by a creation request to the usdPppMlPppLinkConfigTable. The bundleName specified in usdPppMlPppNetworkBundleName must have been created first in the usdPppMlPppBundleTable. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable is created/destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

usdPppMlPppLinkBindTable.name: usdPppMlPppLinkBindTable
usdPppMlPppLinkBindTable.description: This table contains entries for MLPPP Link interface to MLPPP network interfaces bindings.

usdPppMlPppLinkBindEntry.name: usdPppMlPppLinkBindEntry
usdPppMlPppLinkBindEntry.description: Each entry describes the MLPPP link interface to MLPPP network interface bindings.

usdPppMlPppBindNetworkIfIndex.name: usdPppMlPppBindNetworkIfIndex
usdPppMlPppBindNetworkIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the MLPPP network interface.

usdPppMlPppBindLinkIfIndex.name: usdPppMlPppBindLinkIfIndex
usdPppMlPppBindLinkIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of a MLPPP link interface bound by the MLPPP network interface defined by usdPppMlPppBindNetworkIfIndex.

usdPppMlPppBindRowStatus.name: usdPppMlPppBindRowStatus
usdPppMlPppBindRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdPppMlPppBindRowStatus In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: The interfaces identified by usdPppMlPppBindNetworkIfIndex and usdPppMlPppBindLinkIfIndex must be created in the usdPppMlPppNetworkConfigTable and usdPppMlPppLinkConfigTable respectively. A MLPPP bundle must be associated with the usdPppMlPppNetworkIfIndex and exist in the usdPppMibPppBundleTable. A corresponding entry in ifStackTable is created/destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

usdPppSummaryPppInterfaceCount.name: usdPppSummaryPppInterfaceCount
usdPppSummaryPppInterfaceCount.description: The total number of PPP interfaces configured in the system.

usdPppSummaryPppIpNCPs.name: usdPppSummaryPppIpNCPs
usdPppSummaryPppIpNCPs.description: The total number IP NCP's configured in the system.

usdPppSummaryPppOsiNCPs.name: usdPppSummaryPppOsiNCPs
usdPppSummaryPppOsiNCPs.description: The total number of OSI NCP's configured in the system.

usdPppSummaryPppIfAdminUp.name: usdPppSummaryPppIfAdminUp
usdPppSummaryPppIfAdminUp.description: The total number of PPP interfaces in the system that are administratively configured to up(1).

usdPppSummaryPppIfAdminDown.name: usdPppSummaryPppIfAdminDown
